g.text: In this group project we was given the assignment to redesign the streaming and podcast service - LOUD.LAND's website. This project was created through CMS and PHP

In this project my role was mainly directing the design process with different tools and games to enhance cre-ativity and find the best design solutions we would agree on as a group. And creating mockups and prototypes ac-cording to what we had agreed upon.

In this group project we was given the assignment to find a newly started business doing e-commerce, and then redesign their website according to the Busines Model developed from insigths in our own research of the business and the market

We found “Morrow” which is a take-qway platform with no delivery service but with the opportunity to save money when buying the most popular food while the restaurant also saves money by having less waste food. Our solution is created through CMS and pHP, where my main role was guiding the idea- and design process. I was also managing the content production for the site, where we produced a video for the site and one for dis-trubtion on SoMe

In this group project we was given the assignment to make our own configurator where you should be able to change color of different parts of an SVGand also be able to either add or change some parts of the SVG

We chose to make an apartment plan configurator where you are able to add different furniture to the apart-ment and change their color while also being able to keep track of what you have added. In this assingment my main role was coding the different features

svg.text: Take a look at my different projects developed during my study as a Multimedia designer and Frontend developer at KEA. You can also check out my first portfolio with projects from the first semester here (https://1-semester-portfolie.netlify.app/portfolie.html)

In this group project we was given the assignment to invent our own business and develop a website connected to a database with data of our own choise. It should also be possible to filter the data on the website

We chose to make a plant guide called mamaFlora, guid-ing you through the different types of plants and descri-pring the needs of care for each plant. In this project my role was mainly the coding of the filtering options, connecting the database and displaying the data
